| Trivia                  = * Marvel Studios announced ''Ant-Man and the Wasp'' on October 8, 2015, almost a year after the original slate of Phase 3 films in the [[Earth-199999|Marvel Cinematic Universe]] was first announced.{{cite|ref=true|url=http://marvel.com/news/movies/25244/marvel studios phase 3 update|title=Marvel Studios Phase 3 Update|last=Strom|first=Marc|work=Marvel.com|date=8 October 2015|accessdate=8 October 2015}}
* Early on, the film included a flashback scene of Hank Pym and Bill Foster's younger years working together, in which audiences would've been able to actually see Foster growing in size. The idea was scrapped, according to director Peyton Reed, because it was from a narrative perspective "too much of a left turn."{{cite|ref=true|url=https://soundcloud.com/empiremagazine/ant-man-and-the-wasp-spoiler-special|title=Ant-Man And The Wasp Spoiler Special|work=Soundcloud|first=The Empire Film Podcast|date=10 August 2018|accessdate=11 August 2018}}
* Writers [[Chris McKenna]] and [[Erik Sommers]] were told at one point to add a piece of dialogue about [[Hope Van Dyne (Earth-199999)|Hope Van Dyne]] losing her cat, which would have had ramifications in ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]''. McKenna believes it's possible that instead of a rat, Hope's cat would have been responsible for setting up the [[Quantum Tunnel]] to free [[Scott Lang (Earth-199999)|Ant-Man]] from the [[Quantum Realm]].{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/why-spider-man-far-home-nixed-a-donald-glover-cameo-1223627|title='Spider-Man: Far From Home' Team Considered a Donald Glover Cameo|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Aaron|last=Couch|date=13 July 2019|accessdate=19 July 2019}}

